Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.24,0:01:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takahisa-senpai...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.32,0:02:22.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The black knights are just.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.71,0:02:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.87,0:02:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're saying that we're the evil ones!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.13,0:02:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's messed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.34,0:02:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Fragment"...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.22,0:02:34.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. You are "fragments."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.74,0:02:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fragments of the Voidstone{kyomu no maseki 虚無の魔石} that holds enormous magical power.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.34,0:02:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Voidstone...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.39,0:02:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am also one of those "fragments."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.06,0:02:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be exact, one who holds a "fragment."{she's likely means that she has a fragment inbedded into her}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.47,0:02:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are seven fragments.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.25,0:02:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You... Me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.00,0:02:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuka-san... Yukiko-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.89,0:02:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kukuri-san... Takahisa-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.20,0:03:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And finally, the prisoned{captured} Witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.51,0:03:12.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the fragment a demonic essence?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.92,0:03:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fragments themselves aren't necessarily demonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.94,0:03:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, if the seven are to be gathered once again...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.98,0:03:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,their power will be overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.55,0:03:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it all depends on who uses them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.11,0:03:27.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Lisette's objective?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.00,0:03:30.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to collect all seven fragments,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.36,0:03:35.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she called us into her world, the Crimson Night?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.55,0:03:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.93,0:03:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then everything lies with Lisette?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.07,0:03:42.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.16,0:03:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is not her real form.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.75,0:03:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When she was sealed, her powers and memory were taken and she took that form.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.45,0:03:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her real name is Liselotte.{name guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.79,0:03:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Liselotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.36,0:04:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When all seven fragments are gathered, she will be able to grant a wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.20,0:04:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A wish?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.88,0:04:07.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Descent to Hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.90,0:04:11.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What you call the black moon is the Gate of Oblivion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.06,0:04:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is the entrance to Hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.31,0:04:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Liselotte is trying to open the Gate of Oblivion using the powers of the Voidstone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.80,0:04:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the entrance were to open, what'll happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.83,0:04:24.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The world will descend into Hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.27,0:04:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, fall to ruins. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.56,0:04:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.75,0:04:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The world will... fall to ruins...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.53,0:04:37.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And in order to hinder that, the Black Knights are targeting us?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.42,0:04:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to save the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.59,0:04:41.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see that. They're just, aren't they.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.36,0:04:45.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, they already don't have enough fragments left.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.51,0:04:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takahisa...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.06,0:04:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the "fragment" is still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.89,0:04:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as Aeon's Eye exists, the Descent to Hell is still possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.52,0:05:03.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The tea is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.51,0:05:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We also have cookies, Kakeru-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.99,0:05:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, have some.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.72,0:05:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuka...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.33,0:05:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you believe we can win?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.78,0:05:20.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Misuzu-senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.37,0:05:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it, Kakeru-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.03,0:05:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should call her Kusakabe-senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.03,0:05:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Note: Yuka wants Kakeru to call Misuzu in a more formal way: with her last name.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.58,0:05:39.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.67,0:05:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.39,0:05:45.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. I'm a bit tired so I'll just rest a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.87,0:05:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuka, I'll take my tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.13,0:05:50.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.28,0:05:54.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shiori-kun, let's continue our conversation later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.69,0:05:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.69,0:06:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you fine without resting either, Kakeru-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.72,0:06:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're tired, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.55,0:06:03.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.76,0:06:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we can sleep together, like we did in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.55,0:06:10.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot. What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.36,0:06:16.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? Your face is going red.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.71,0:06:17.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're strange, Kakeru-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.86,0:06:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The world will fall to ruin...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.01,0:06:32.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's just way too much for me to absorb right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.35,0:06:35.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kakeru-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.58,0:06:40.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yuka?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.10,0:06:45.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's sleep together.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.47,0:06:46.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.76,0:06:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let her sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.96,0:06:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you do so, then I can continue my story.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.60,0:07:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A hundred years in the past, a single magician obtained an immortal body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.59,0:07:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People called her the Witch of Babylon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.38,0:07:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They feared and hated her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.53,0:07:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's Liselotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.43,0:07:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, the Witch met with a young king and fell in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.71,0:07:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The name of that king was Verard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.28,0:07:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At that time, the storm of civil war was sweeping through the county of Dravenia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.36,0:08:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This world should just fall to ruin.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.42,0:08:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. We don't need this kind of world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.85,0:08:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need anything as long as I have you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.22,0:08:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kakeru-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.89,0:08:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards, Verard was felled by one of his trusted friend's retainers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.54,0:08:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He lost his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.69,0:08:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lisellote wept when she learned of his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.24,0:08:40.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so she swore:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.72,0:08:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I will fulfill my loved one's wish with my hands."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.52,0:08:53.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Descent to Hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.00,0:08:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so we, the Holy Ministry of the Index Librorum Prohibitorum,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.03,0:09:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,have traversed time and fought with those allied with the Witch that brings misfortune to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.69,0:09:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, 64 years before the present,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.19,0:09:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we succeeded at last in sealing her into an alternate world...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.60,0:09:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...in this very land.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.77,0:09:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why the Crimson Night is in this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.55,0:09:30.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the people who risked their lives to fight for the Holy Ministry of the Index Librorum Probitorum Holy Ministry have,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.50,0:09:38.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as a price for sealing her, been transformed into grotesque forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.50,0:09:43.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The black knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.41,0:09:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are protecting the Witch's seal in the alternate world holding Liselotte in which you call the Crimson Night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.48,0:09:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what this was all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.69,0:09:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kakeru-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.93,0:10:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The blacks knights believe that Verard will eventually awaken within you, take over your body, and help the Witch using the Aeon's Eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.86,0:10:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why they want to kill you before that happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.90,0:10:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Verard will take over my body...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.23,0:10:15.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is what our Holy Ministry believes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.72,0:10:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the Aeon's Eye, it is possible to not only seal, \Nbut get rid of the immortal Witch in time altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.99,0:10:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason why I had observed without revealing myself was to determine whether you're a human to be doubted, or...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.58,0:10:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you're a human that can be trusted with the world's future.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.22,0:10:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the answer is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.24,0:10:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had thought, "What a naive and weak human this is."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.41,0:10:52.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Such a human would surely have their soul and body stolen by Verard, as we thought."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.92,0:10:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have come to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.87,0:11:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I too have been pessimistic of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.70,0:11:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"What a pointless world," I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.23,0:11:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, after getting assigned this task, I had thought that had worse come to worst, then it would be my fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.41,0:11:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.70,0:11:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had come to know that this world and its people still had plenty of life within.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.75,0:11:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, there's an idiot sleeping during class!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.37,0:11:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore I will believe in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.71,0:11:40.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You who lives in this world, creates bonds \Nbetween people, and embraces tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.09,0:11:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For friends and for tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.57,0:11:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.41,0:11:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to. If it is possible, I want to protect this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.56,0:11:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Shiori-san, had it been yesterday, I believe that I could have answered that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.37,0:11:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That it was all right because I had friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.78,0:12:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... now it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.34,0:12:09.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we're... all in pieces{helter skelter, chaotic}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.49,0:12:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tachibana-senpai...
